<%# ── FAQ ── %>
<div class="border-t border-slate-800 py-16">
  <h2 class="text-center text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-10">Frequently asked questions</h2>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">What is a stem separator?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">A stem separator uses AI to split a mixed song into its individual components — vocals, bass, drums, and other instruments. This lets producers, DJs, and musicians work with individual parts of a track for remixing, sampling, flipping, or practice.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">Do I need a subscription?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">No. demucs:r is completely free to use. No monthly fees, no commitments.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">What stems does it extract?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Every track is separated into four stems: bass, drums, vocals, and other (synth/guitar). All stems are delivered as WAV files.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">What audio formats are supported?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">WAV, MP3, FLAC, and OGG files up to 500 MB.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">Does it work on mobile, tablet, and Linux?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Yes. All processing happens on our servers so demucs:r works in any browser — iPhone, Android, iPad, Mac, Windows, and Linux. No app or installation needed.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">How long does processing take?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Most tracks are ready within a few minutes. You'll get an email when your stems are ready to download.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">How long are stems stored?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Stems are available for 24 hours after processing. Download them before then — they're permanently deleted after that window.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-white text-sm font-medium mb-1">What AI model does it use?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">demucs:r uses Meta's open-source demucs model — one of the highest quality stem separation models available. The High Quality tier uses htdemucs_ft, a fine-tuned version optimised for music production use cases.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

